[[div class="echo"]]
You think you've maybe found something you would like to buy -- or at least, ask about. It lays heavy in your hand, cold as metal, no price tag in sight.

You're going to have to talk to the owner. Good luck.

As you approach the store counter, you are shocked with how quickly you ended up back here. As if noticing your vacant stare, the owner speaks.

"Yeah, the store does that. If you want to buy something, it helps you find the counter. Don't ask me how or why, it was like that when I bought the place. Now, did you find something you liked?

You go to put the trinket on the counter, when you realize -- your hand is empty. Embarrassed, you start looking around in a panic. Did you drop it?

"Don't worry about it. The store decided it didn't want you to buy that -- again, she does what she wants. Can I interest you in any of the trinkets made by local artisans? I helped too, you know, but it wouldn't have been possible without them."
